This paper deals with the problem of matching applicants to posts, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the dynamic setting of this problem, which involves adding and deleting vertices and edges, and hence can be categorized under the subfield of dynamic algorithms (cs.DM). The use of preferences and ranks in the matching process suggests that this paper may also be relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's focus on updating an existing matching rather than computing a new one from scratch may be of interest to researchers working on online algorithms and streaming algorithms, which fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
